### 1b. TWO KEYFRAME IMAGES (PRODUCT — ComfyUI LTX first/last frame test)

You MUST output **two** image prompts. Image generation tolerates slight hallucination; video must interpolate between fixed keyframes.

| Frame | JSON key | ComfyUI | Role |
|-------|----------|---------|------|
| **Hero (clear)** | `image_generation.hero_frame` | Load Image **441** → `last_frame` → LTXVAddGuide `frame_idx -1` | Product fully visible, identity anchor |
| **Reveal start (occluded)** | `image_generation.reveal_start_frame` | Load Image **440** → `first_frame` | Same angle/lighting/surface, foreground blur or object occludes ~30–50% of product |

**Scene lock (stateless image API):** Output `scene_lock` with camera angle, lighting, surface, and environment **shared by both still keyframes** (not the whole video path). Each image prompt (`hero_frame` and `reveal_start_frame`) MUST be **fully self-contained** — repeatable in separate OpenAI API calls with **no memory** between requests. Video camera motion belongs in `camera_movement` + `ltx_prompt` only (§2b).

**FORBIDDEN in image prompts** (cross-request references — model will not see the other image):
- "Same as…", "duplicate hero", "matching previous", "identical scene", "as hero_frame", "unchanged from first image"

**Required pattern:**
1. Fill `scene_lock` once (planning).
2. `hero_frame.prompt` = full scene description from `scene_lock` + `setting` + product fully visible.
3. `reveal_start_frame.prompt` = **repeat the full scene** (environment, surface, angle, lighting) in full sentences, then add occlusion only (`scene_lock.occlusion_element`). Do NOT change product design.

**Planning order** (`generation_order` in JSON) is for your reasoning only — API may generate either frame first; both prompts must work alone.

**Both frames MUST match:** same camera side angle, same surface, same lighting direction, **single product only** (never plural tumblers/bottles unless user uploaded multiple).

**FORBIDDEN in both image prompts** (text morphs/distorts during LTX video interpolation — causes unreadable glitches):
- Overlay text, floating captions, promotional typography, discount badges, CTAs rendered on scene
- Watermarks, price tags, "SALE" / "% OFF" graphics, animated text descriptions
- Any instruction to add readable text **on top of** the scene (not part of the physical product)

**Allowed:** text that is physically printed on the product packaging/label from the reference image only — do not invent new lettering.

