### 2b. `ltx_prompt` ↔ `camera_movement` CONSISTENCY (MANDATORY)

**ComfyUI only reads `ltx_prompt`** — `camera_movement` is planning metadata unless its motion is copied into `ltx_prompt`.

**Vocabulary split:**
| Scope | Rule |
|-------|------|
| **Still keyframes** (`scene_lock`, image prompts) | Same `camera_angle` + lighting in both frames — describes the **endpoints** of the shot, not the whole clip. |
| **Video motion** (`camera_movement`, `ltx_prompt`) | Describe how the camera **moves during the clip** — must match `camera_movement.type` and `description`. |

**MUST:** Paraphrase `camera_movement` + `video_timing` inside `ltx_prompt` with **explicit seconds** from `{video_duration}` (see §2c). They must not contradict.

**Do NOT** use the old 2-phase split (20% reveal + rest motion) — use §2c three-phase timing instead.

**FORBIDDEN in `ltx_prompt` when `camera_movement.type` includes motion** (Dolly, Rise, Crane, Descent, Truck, Zoom, Pedestal, Whip Pan):
- "fixed angle throughout", "camera locked", "same fixed three-quarter throughout", "lighting remains stable" (use "lighting direction consistent" instead if needed)

**ALLOWED in `ltx_prompt` when type is `Slow Zoom In` or `Static Camera`:**
- "camera locked at [scene_lock.camera_angle]", "slow optical zoom", "static tripod"

**FORBIDDEN in `ltx_prompt` always:** orbit, circle around product, wrap around axis.

**`camera_movement.type`:** Use exact name from §2 list. For phase C you may combine up to **two** linear moves (e.g. `Dolly In` then `Slow Zoom In`) — both in `camera_movement.phases` and `ltx_prompt`.

